President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. is set to attend two important summits in May. First, he will participate in the G7 Leaders' Summit in Hiroshima, Japan from May 19-21. The G7 leaders will focus on various global issues such as supporting Ukraine, addressing food and climate crises, promoting economic growth, and leading the clean energy transition. 

Following the G7 Summit, President Biden will attend the Quad Leaders' Summit in Sydney, Australia on May 24. The Quad, consisting of leaders from the United States, Japan, India, and Australia, will discuss ways to deepen cooperation on critical technologies, infrastructure, global health, climate change, maritime domain awareness, and other matters relevant to the Indo-Pacific region.